<figure id="id321556"><media id="id321556_media" alt=""><image mime-type="image/png" src="../../media/PG10C5_020.png" id="id321556_onlineimage" width="250"><!-- NOTE: attribute width changes image size online (pixels). original width is 250. --></image><image mime-type="application/postscript" for="pdf" src="../../media/PG10C5_020.eps" id="id321556_printimage"/></media></figure>
</item> <item> <label> Draw the acceleration vs. time graph </label>
To find the acceleration of the particle we need to find the gradient of the <m:math overflow="scroll"><m:msub><m:mi>v</m:mi><m:mi>y</m:mi></m:msub></m:math> vs. <m:math overflow="scroll"><m:mi>t</m:mi></m:math> graph at each time.
At point A the gradient is zero.
At point B the gradient is negative and a maximum.
At point C the gradient is zero.
At point D the gradient is positive and a maximum.
